cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with robust PCA, which is a common technique in machine learning for dimensionality reduction. It also involves optimization and convergence analysis, which are important topics in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as PCA is widely used in computer vision for feature extraction and image compression. 

The paper also involves matrix factorization and projection, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory). 

The use of truncated SVD and low dimensional subspace projection suggests that the paper could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). 

Finally, the paper involves algorithm design and performance evaluation, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
